As of the current state, 19 out of the 27 member states of the European Union have adopted the Euro as their official currency. These countries include Austria, Belgium, Cyprus, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Ireland, Italy, Latvia, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, the Netherlands, Portugal, Slovakia, Slovenia, and Spain. These nations replaced their national currencies with the Euro in the following dates: 

- 1999: euro currency introduction (for cash); 
- 2002: euro coins; 
- The national currencies remaining in circulation until 2002: Austrian schilling (February 1, 2002), Belgian franc (January 1, 2002), Cypriot pound (January 1, 2008), Estonian króna (January 1, 2011), Finnish markka (January 1, 2002), French franc (January 1, 2002), German mark (January 1, 2002), Greek drachma (January 1, 2002), Irish pound (January 1, 2002), Italian lira (January 1, 2002), Latvian lats (January 1, 2014), Lithuanian litas (January 1, 2015), Luxembourgish franc (January 1, 2002), Maltese lira (January 1, 2008), Portuguese escudo (January 1, 2002), Slovak koruna (January 1, 2009), Slovenian tolar (January 1, 2007), and Spanish peseta (January 1, 2002).

Medimmune, Inc. is a pharmaceutical company that specializes in developing and commercializing innovative products for the treatment of chronic and rare diseases. Their product portfolio includes several well-known medications, such as SYMLARIN, a treatment for chronic rhinitis and allergic asthma, and BENLYSTA, a medication for rheumatoid arthritis and other autoimmune disorders. Additionally, Medimmune has a product pipeline that includes several therapeutic candidates in various stages of development, including a CD19-directed CAR-T therapy for the treatment of aggressive B-cell lymphoma, and a novel immunosuppressant for prevention of organ rejection in solid organ transplantation.

As of 2022, the company's product portfolio primarily focuses on the development of monoclonal antibodies for the treatment of various indications, including respiratory, dermatological, and autoimmune diseases. Some of the main products in their pipeline are:

* MEDI5757, a novel checkpoint inhibitor for the treatment of various types of cancer;
* MEDI8897, a respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) vaccine for the prevention of RSV disease;
* MEDI9360, a novel immunotherapeutic agent for the treatment of various types of cancer;
* MEDI4920, a CD39-targeting antibody for the treatment of various autoimmune and inflammatory diseases.

